{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"85d789a0-14ec-4702-98e7-ee88e6abf4ed","content":"This is a known Android 15 (API 35) breaking change. `SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE` is **ignored** starting with API 35, and .NET 10 targets it by default. The replacement is the `WindowInsets` IME API.\n\n**Fix — update `Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs`:**\n\n```csharp\nusing Android.Views;\nusing AndroidX.Core.View;\n\n[Activity(Theme = \"@style/Maui.SplashTheme\", MainLauncher = true,\n    ConfigurationChanges = /* ... existing flags ... */,\n    WindowSoftInputMode = SoftInput.AdjustNothing)]\npublic class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity\n{\n    protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)\n    {\n        base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);\n\n        var content = FindViewById(Android.Resource.Id.Content)!;\n        ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(content, new ImeInsetsListener());\n    }\n\n    private class ImeInsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener\n    {\n        public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(View v, WindowInsetsCompat insets)\n        {\n            var ime = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());\n            var bars = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.SystemBars());\n\n            // Use whichever bottom inset is larger — keyboard or nav bar\n            v.SetPadding(v.PaddingLeft, v.PaddingTop, v.PaddingRight,\n                Math.Max(ime.Bottom, bars.Bottom));\n\n            return insets;\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Why this works:**\n\n| .NET 9 (API 34) | .NET 10 (API 35+) |\n|---|---|\n| `AdjustResize` shrinks the window | `AdjustResize` is **ignored** |\n| System handles layout shift | You must react to `WindowInsets` yourself |\n\nThe `IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener` fires whenever the keyboard opens/closes. It reads the IME (keyboard) bottom inset and applies matching padding to your content view, pushing your input bar up above the keyboard.\n\n**Tip:** If you want a smooth animated slide (not a jump), replace the listener with a `WindowInsetsAnimationCompat.Callback` to interpolate padding frame-by-frame during the keyboard animation.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"143b17c2-2c63-4a92-835d-aadf1b1ce856","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a .NET MAUI issue where the keyboard covers the text input at the bottom of the screen. They mention that `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` worked in .NET 9 but doesn't work in .NET 10.\n\nThis is a known change in .NET MAUI. In .NET 10 (which targets Android API 35+), edge-to-edge display is enforced, and the old `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` approach was deprecated. The new approach involves using `WindowInsets` and the `Ime` inset type to handle keyboard visibility.\n\n\nFor .NET 10 and Android 15+, I need to explain that `SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE` is no longer effective due to edge-to-edge enforcement, and the modern solution involves listening to `WindowInsets` changes to detect when the keyboard appears and adjust the layout padding accordingly. Setting up a window insets listener to handle keyboard appearance on Android, then considering the built-in `KeyboardAutoManagerScroll` feature in MAUI 9+ as an alternative, though it has some limitations. The real shift in .NET 10 is that edge-to-edge rendering is now the default on Android 15+, which changes how the framework handles keyboard insets. a workaround, though it just pans the window up rather than resizing it. The real solution involves using platform-specific insets listeners for proper behavior. Since `SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE` was deprecated in API 30 and is completely ignored in API 35, and .NET 10 targets API 35 by default, I need to show how to handle `WindowInsets` IME insets through a custom handler or platform-specific code in the Android project.\n\nSetting up the insets listener... Finishing the inset calculation...","outputTokens":1982,"requestId":"9813:A3554:1C11568:1F1136C:6A05212E"},"id":"7f2b2486-1676-4dbf-b377-8292a733f1fb","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:11:45.544Z","parentId":"87947114-4110-4198-b561-a6c1568c56c6"}
